SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c03661318
Version: 1

HPSBST02846 SSRT100798 rev.1 - HP LeftHand Virtual SAN Appliance hydra,
Remote Execution of Arbitrary Code

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2013-02-05
Last Updated: 2013-02-05

Potential Security Impact: Remote execution of arbitrary code

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified with HP LeftHand
Virtual SAN Appliance hydra. The vulnerabilities could be remotely exploited
resulting in execution of arbitrary code.

References: ZDI-CAN-1468 (CVE-2012-3282, SSRT100722), ZDI-CAN-1511
(CVE-2012-3283, SSRT100798), ZDI-CAN-1512 (CVE-2012-3284, SSRT100799),
ZDI-CAN-1513 (CVE-2012-3285, SSRT100800),

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP LeftHand Virtual SAN Appliance software prior to version 10.0.

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2012-3282    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       10.0
CVE-2012-3283    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       10.0
CVE-2012-3284    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       10.0
CVE-2012-3285    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       10.0
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

The Hewlett-Packard Company thanks TippingPoint's Zero Day Initiative for
reporting ZDI-CAN-1468, ZDI-CAN-1511, ZDI-CAN-1512, and ZDI-CAN-1513 to
security-alert@...com

RESOLUTION

HP has made the following updates available to resolve the vulnerabilities.

Please contact HP for any necessary assistance to update HP LeftHand Virtual
SAN Appliance software to version 10.0 or subsequent.

